    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "🧠 Hypothesis"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YTel4VF0H87M"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "When the price moves below the lower Bollinger Band, it indicates the stock is oversold and likely to revert upward.\n",
        "Similarly, when the price moves above the upper Bollinger Band, it indicates the stock is overbought and likely to revert downward."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6DcGCCFAIDNz"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "⚙️ Implementation"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mSBSx5ccIAac"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "A trade is initiated when the stock price crosses below the lower Bollinger Band.\n",
        "\n",
        "The position is held until the price crosses above the upper Bollinger Band, at which point the trade is exited.\n",
        "\n",
        "All trades are executed using closing prices, and returns are calculated on a per-trade basis."
